Wash and dry all produce. Adjust rack to upper position and preheat oven to 450 degrees. Cut @Yukon Gold Potatoes{12%ounces} into ½-inch cubes. Toss on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @olive oil{1%tsp} and a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}. Roast in oven until browned and tender, ~{20-25%minutes}, tossing halfway through.

Meanwhile, halve, peel, and finely dice @Yellow Onion{1}. Remove and discard stems and large ribs from @Collard Greens{8%ounces}. Roughly chop leaves. Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{1%tsp} in a large #pan{} over medium heat. Add onion and cook, tossing, until softened, ~{4-5%minutes}. Remove a quarter of the onion from pan and set aside.

Toss collard greens into pan. Pour in @water{1/4%cup}, cover pan, and cook until softened, ~{3-4%minutes}. Uncover and toss until leaves are tender and water evaporates, another ~{2-3%minutes}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Remove from pan and set aside.

> Use foil to cover your pan if it doesn't have a lid.

Measure out ¼ cup @Flour{1/4%cup} (we sent more) and set aside 1 tsp for gravy. Toss remainder of the flour and @Cajun Spice Blend{1%tablespoon} in a shallow #dish{}. Heat a large drizzle of @olive oil{2%tsp} in same pan over medium heat. Season @Pork Chops{12%ounces} with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Toss in flour mixture to coat, shaking off excess. Add to pan. Cook to desired doneness, ~{3-6%minutes} per side. Remove from pan and let rest ~{5%minutes}.

While pork rests, wipe out pan. Return pan to medium heat and add a drizzle of @olive oil{1%tsp}, reserved onion, and reserved 1 tsp flour. Cook, tossing, until flour loses its raw smell, ~{1-2%minutes}. Stir in @Chicken Stock Concentrate{1} and @water{1/3%cup}. Bring to a simmer and let bubble until reduced by half, ~{2-3%minutes}. Remove from heat and stir in @Sour Cream{2%tablespoons}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Toss collard greens with potatoes on baking sheet. Return to oven and allow to warm through, ~{1-2%minutes}. Divide between plates, then top with pork. Spoon gravy over and serve.